column5: After Dad lost about a 4 lber, he caught 3 to My None, but then I crept  back to a 5 to 4 lead,  not that anyone was keeping track, accept him. Dad got the biggest just over 20" nice way to end the season, one of the better day's he had this fall, water was 42.5 degrees, caught on tubes again in 7.5' to 10' of water, fished from 12:30 til 4:30pm
Love the colour of those Green backs  Nice fishing Guys
Awesome way to end the season Richard Congrats to both of you Thanks for sharing Leechman
I know that I have not been a member here for long, but I don't remember so many brilliant smallie reports especially this late. Nice job!! Jim

we got skunked down here today.... tried fishing the tubes real sloooooww.... and then slower... tried dragging  a texas rigged senko.. slooooowwwww... naddaa...  oh well.. I have an early day tomorrow,,, gonna fish the last day of the season in the rain and snow I just want ONE more largie.... not that my NICKEL there last week was a bad way to end the season for me
Looks like a great day to finish off the season

Bass till the bitter end....gotta love it. November bass this year was great for me as well. I had the best two days of bass fishing of my life this November. I will post the pics for everybody when I get all the pics from my buddys camara. Here is one of many November largies   .
Sweet looking largie, what you catch it on Richard
